gomodel:SYNGO_5114  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4, 5: SPIN90 (NCKIPSD) phosphorylation increased its postsynaptic localization and binds PSD95 (DLG4) and Shank with increased efficiency.\n\nFigure 6:\n\"Cultured hippocampal neurons were transfected with GFP empty vector or GFP-SPIN90 WT, YE or YF at DIV 10-12 and spine head widths and lengths were analyzed at DIV 19-21. Co-transfection of RDF-actin enabled the spine morphology to be visualized. Spine head width was markedly increased in SPIN90 WT and YE-transfected cells, as compared with SPIN90 YF- and GFP-transfected cells, and spine length was slightly greater in SPIN90 YE-transfected cells than in SPIN90 WT- and YF-transfected cells (Fig. 6A,B). This suggests that SPIN90 phosphorylation contributes to the regulation of dendritic spine enlargement.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"Rat hippocampal neurons transfected with GFP-SPIN90 at DIV 10-12 were fixed at DIV 19-21 and labeled with the indicated antibodies\"\n\nantibody:\nPolyclonal anti-SPIN90 serum was described previously PMID:21763308" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5114" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

